<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The function lfs_mlist_isopen takes both head and node as non-const pointers although it only reads the list and does not modify any nodes. For example, the signature "static bool lfs_mlist_isopen(struct lfs_mlist *head, struct lfs_mlist *node)" and the declaration "struct lfs_mlist **p = &head" use non-const pointer types even though a traversal using a single pointer (e.g. "const struct lfs_mlist *p = head; p = p->next;") would allow head and node to be const-qualified. Therefore the parameters could (and should) be declared as const struct lfs_mlist *head and const struct lfs_mlist *node to satisfy MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>

